#!/usr/bin/perl -w

use xPL::Dock qw/-run/;

=head1 NAME

xpl-fdnotify - Perl script for an xPL X OSD application

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  xpl-fdnotify [flags] [options]
  where valid flags are:
    --help         - show this help text
    --verbose      - verbose mode (for the xPL layer)
    --fdnotify-verbose - verbose mode (for the X OSD layer)
  and valid options are (default shown in brackets):
    --interface if0       - the interface for xPL messages (first
                            non-loopback or loopback)

  # start the notify client on first ethernet interface in verbose mode
  xpl-fdnotify --verbose --fdnotify-verbose

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This script is an xPL client that displays xPL C<osd.basic> messages using
freedesktop notification service.

=head1 SEE ALSO

xPL::Dock(3), xPL::Dock::FDNotify(3)

Project website: http://www.xpl-perl.org.uk/

